    "(9) TANR (Wu et al. 2019d): A model that jointly learns topic-aware news and user representations using latent topics inferred from user behavior.",
    "(10) HieRec (Qi et al. 2021): A hierarchical user modeling framework that encodes preferences at multiple levels for better personalization.",
    "(11) MINER (Li et al. 2022): A modular architecture that integrates multiple views and selectors to dynamically capture diverse user reading patterns.",
    "Table 3 presents the performance of Co-NAML-LSTUR against a broad range of baseline methods on both MINDsmall and MIND-large datasets.",
    "We compare against both traditional recommendation methods (LibFM, DeepFM) and a range of neural news recommenders, including contentbased models (NRMS, LSTUR, NAML, DKN), attentionbased models (NPA, TANR), and recent state-of-the-art frameworks (HieRec, MINER)."
